SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 121
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Lucas Hilliard to
the standards recommendation committee for
English language arts.
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-1-312, creates a standards
recommendation committee for English language arts; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-1-312(a), provides that the
governor shall appoint four members to the standards recommendation committee for English
language arts; and
WHEREAS, Governor Bill Lee has appointed Lucas Hilliard to serve on such committee
for a term that expires on December 31, 2025; and
WHEREAS, an educator since 2019, Mr. Hilliard teaches at White House High School in
Sumner County, where he has taught English II, English III, AP English Literature and
Composition, AP English Language and Composition, AP Seminar, and AP Research; and
WHEREAS, he is a 2016 graduate of Vanderbilt University and holds a master's degree
in education from Union University; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-1-312(b), provides that all
appointments to the committee "shall be subject to confirmation by the senate and the house of
representatives"; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we confirm the appointment of Lucas Hilliard to the
standards recommendation committee for English language arts for a term that expires on
December 31, 2025.
